Messages can be one of two kinds: Operations and Administration Messages.

Operations:
	- add/3
		Arguments:
			lineid - the id of the line where the add occured
			index - start insertion position within the line
			string - string to insert
	- del/2
		Arguments:
			lineid - the id of the line where the del occured
			index - start deletion position within the line
			lenght - number of characters to delete
	- rep/3
		Arguments:
			lineid - the id of the line where the del occured
			index - start replacement position
			lenght - number of characters to delete
			string - string to insert after replacement position
	- newLine/2
		Arguments:
			lineid - the id of the new line
			text - the line itself
	- delLine/1
		Arguments:
			lineid - the id of the line to delete
			
Administration Messages (not finished):
	- newUser/2
		Arguments:
			username - username of the new user
			color - the rgb code associated with the respective user
	- newMsg/2
		Arguments:
			username - username of the creator of the message
			msg - the message itself
	- exitUser/1
		Arguments:
			username - the username of the user that has abandoned the group
	- exit/0
			
			
The messages are sent using JSON.
Example operation - add(2,asdasd) on state 11,2 :

---
{
    "msg": [
        {
            "operation": [
                {
                    "_type": "add",
                    "_args": [
						1_1_20110125003951818_7,
                        1,
                        "asdf"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "_type": "add",
                    "_args": [
						1_1_20110125003951818_7,
                        1,
                        "asdf"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "state": [
                11,
                2
            ]
        }
    ]
}
---
